I imagined I would give three stars to this place when I walked in. The place isn’t the prettiest and looks very busy. But when I was served, it changed my mind. The amount of food you get is just out of this world (in the picture, everything cost a total of less $10).This place is not your typical chinese takeout. If you order to stay, you have an array of tables (around 20) to sit and enjoy your meal. They serve tea to every customer even before he or she orders food. The food is okay, but if you are looking to fill yourself up to the brim, this is the perfect place. The staff is friendly and service is fast. The servers kept coming to check my table in case I meed something.

My work lunch crew visits often.  The decor is less than desirable but they have about 10 seating booths which seats 4 into a booth, plus regular tables.  It is a little shabby but the food is always savory and delicious.  Try the Triple Crown dish.  Service of hot tea when staying is great for those watching soda intake.  There is a ten min wait for the food but its not instant ramen.  Wink wink.  The price in the middle range and you get fresh food.  In addition, the only chinese in the neighhood with good rating from Dept of Health.  3.5 out of 5 stars.
